<h1>Circle Magic</h1>
<p>Cirlce Magic is based on the Cosmological understanding of the 5 Planes as a series of interconnected rings, with the Material ring in the center, with the others connected to each other through the Material Plane.</p>
<p>Circle Magic tends to be more focused and easier to cast then <a href="/Rules/Magic/FreeFormMagic">Free Form Magic</a> but is more controlled and directly powerful then <a href="/Rules/Magic/SpecializedMagic/">Specialized Magic</a></p>
<p>Circle Magic is divided into the 5 main cirlces or planes, and have a series of spells based off of them. Though the specific spells depend on which school taught you.</p>
<p>To cast a circle magic spell, you Roll PSI+(The skill for the ring you are using) + Modifiers 6+ to cast your spells. </p>
<p>Failing to cast a spell results in the caster rolling on the <a href="/Rules/Magic/Perils">Perils Table</a></p>
<h2>Witcher Cirlce Magic</h2>
<p>Witcher Cirlce Magic focuses on being useful for monster hunting and dealing with the supernatural. In brackets is the Free Form Versian version of the spell</p>
<p>If the name has a [T] next to it, it means that the spell is a touch spell.</p>
<h3>Void Ring</h3>
<p>The Void ring represents the ring of creation and the Void Plane.</p>
<ul>
    <li>Throw Fire - Throw a small amount of fire, making a Dex + Effect range attack. (Saptium Aedificate Ignis)</li>
    <li>Throw Water - Throw a small amount of water, making a Dex + Effect range attack. (Saptium Aedificate Liquidum)</li>
    <li>Throw Electricity - Throw a small amount of , electricity making a Dex + Effect range attack. (Saptium Aedificate Vestibulum)</li>
    <li>Push Air - push some air, if someone wishes to resist, they must make an Str/End 8+ check. (Saptium Mutare Aura)</li>
    <li>Pull Air - pull some air, if someone wishes to resist, they must make an Str/End 8+ check. (Saptium Mutare Aura)</li>
    <li>Create Void Energy Shield[T] - Create a shield of void energy able to absorb PSI Points + Effect D * 10 Damage. Lasts for 2D8+Effect minutes (Saptium Aedificate Vis)</li>
</ul>

